

Prerequisites
Outline the information required before proceeding with the listed procedure
Access to Tenfold Resources

Jira 
https://l-p.atlassian.net/browse/TFCO-6791 - Dev one

Procedure
Steps-1:
	Add url to Google auth console
		- Go to the GCP Console, click on the navigation menu.
		- Select APIs and Services → Credentials → under OAuth → add in respective web client

Steps-2: 
Create namespace from bastion host on respective environment
	kubectl create namespace kafka-ui

Steps-3: 
Create and update value.yaml file 
Fill with  cluster, auth and RBAC details as per requirement
For Auth:
		Go to the GCP Console, click on the navigation menu.
		Select APIs and Services → Credentials

YAML details:
---
service:
  type: LoadBalancer
  nodePort: <>
yamlApplicationConfig:
  kafka:
    clusters:
      - name: dev
        bootstrapServers: 
<server1 name>:9092,<server2 name>:9092, … , <serverN name>:9092
  auth:
    type: OAUTH2
    oauth2:
      client:
        google:
          provider: google
          clientId: <>
          clientSecret: <>
          user-name-attribute: email
          redirect-uri: <>
          custom-params:
            type: google
            allowedDomain: <>
  rbac:
    roles:
      - name: admins
        clusters:
          - <environment name>
        subjects:
          - provider: oauth_google
            type: user
            value: <user-id>
          - provider: oauth_google
            type: user
            value: <user-id>
        permissions:
          - resource: applicationconfig
            actions: all
          - resource: clusterconfig
            actions: all
          - resource: topic
            value: .*
            actions: all
          - resource: consumer
            value: .*
            actions: all
          - resource: schema
            value: .*
            actions: all
          - resource: connect
            value: .*
            actions: all
          - resource: ksql
            actions: all
          - resource: acl
            actions: all
      - name: readonly
        clusters:
          - <environment name>
        subjects:
          - provider: oauth_google
            type: domain
            value: "example.com"
        permissions:
          - resource: clusterconfig
            actions:
              - view
          - resource: topic
            value: .*
            actions:
              - VIEW
              - MESSAGES_READ
          - resource: consumer
            value: .*
            actions:
              - view
          - resource: schema
            value: .*
            actions:
              - view
          - resource: connect
            value: .*
            actions:
              - view
          - resource: acl
            actions:
              - view
  management:
    health:
      ldap:
        enabled: false

Steps-4: 
Add the repo from document https://docs.kafka-ui.provectus.io/configuration/helm-charts/quick-start
	helm repo add kafka-ui https://provectus.github.io/kafka-ui-charts
Install kafka-ui
	helm upgrade -i kafka-ui kafka-ui/kafka-ui -n kafka-ui -f values.yaml

Steps-5: 
Create Load Balancer in GCP console on respective environment
- Go to the GCP Console, click on the navigation menu.
- Select Network services → Load Balancer
- Click on create load balancer, fill details for frontend, backend services and health check details.
- Save the load balancer.
Once up the service, add new Port to load balancer backend services and health check.

Steps-6:    
Create firewall rule
In Dev firewall rule: https://console.cloud.google.com/net-security/firewall-manager/firewall-policies/details/kafka-ui-allow?project=tenfold-developer
Add ip to WAF rule
Create DNS name in AWS route53



